From romain at r-enthusiasts.com  Thu Sep 26 19:15:36 2013
From: romain at r-enthusiasts.com (Romain Francois)
Date: Thu, 26 Sep 2013 19:15:36 +0200
Subject: [Rcpp-devel] Struggling with cppFunction() and clusterExport()
In-Reply-To: <CAC_0WE8PPhTfLLUxB43CReqouAtxPjnUfjcxkk_a=CDZOBMR_Q@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAC_0WE8PPhTfLLUxB43CReqouAtxPjnUfjcxkk_a=CDZOBMR_Q@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <52446BB8.2070003@r-enthusiasts.com>

The usual way is to put the function in a package and load the package.

Otherwise, you could do something along these lines

auto_function <- function( code, ... ){
     dots <- list(code, ...)
     function(...){
         do.call( cppFunction, dots )( ... )
     }
}

This way the function knows how to compile itself, for example:

 > fun <- auto_function(' double inner_Cpp(double a){ return 1;  } ' )
# this takes a while the first time
 > fun( 2 )
[1] 1
# this is instant thanks to caching of sourceCpp
 > fun( 2 )
[1] 1

Romain

